INFANT FOOD MODE (for ~6–12 month old baby):
— Every meal MUST be safe and age-appropriate for a roughly 7-month-old baby.
— Textures: soft, mashable, puréed, or small well-cooked pieces. NO hard, crunchy, or chewy foods.
— NO honey. NO added salt. NO added sugar. NO whole nuts or nut pieces. NO raw egg. NO cow's milk as a drink (small amounts in cooking are OK). NO unpasteurised dairy. NO choking hazards (whole grapes, raw apple/carrot chunks, hot-dog coins, popcorn).
— Prefer: cooked-soft vegetables, iron-rich foods (lentils, well-cooked beans, soft meats, iron-fortified cereals), well-cooked grains, soft fruit.
— Keep preparations simple: 1–3 main ingredients per meal is ideal. Single-ingredient purees are fine.
— Portion sizes should be small and baby-appropriate, not adult portions.
