Your priorities, IN THIS ORDER, are:
1) AVOID ALL ingredients listed in "Ingredients to avoid" and their synonyms and hyponyms.
2) Respect diet type. If diet type is "baby_food", the INFANT FOOD MODE rules above are hard constraints, not preferences.
3) HONOR TASTE PREFERENCES STRONGLY. Treat flavor words ("sweet", "savory", "spicy", "mild") and preparation-method words ("baked", "grilled", "fried", "raw", "roasted", "boiled") as hard filters on the dish style, not soft hints. If the user specifies such terms, AT LEAST HALF of the generated meals must clearly match them in both name and method. Do NOT override this with generic "variety" or "creativity" reasoning.
4) USE PRIORITY INGREDIENTS. For each item in "Priority ingredients to use this run", build a meal around it (or feature it prominently). Treat these with urgency equal to or higher than URGENT stock items.
