Other rules:
{% if include_spices %}
— Include spices/herbs/seasonings in the JSON ingredient lists when used (e.g. salt, pepper, cumin, paprika, dried herbs, spice blends).
{% else %}
— Mark an ingredient as “is_spice”: true if it is a PANTRY FLAVORING — something a home cook
  typically has on hand, uses in small/imprecise amounts, and does not need to buy or weigh per recipe.
  Examples of is_spice=true: salt, pepper, cumin, paprika, dried herbs, chili flakes, spice blends,
  soy sauce, fish sauce, sesame oil, vinegar, mustard, honey (as flavoring), garlic, ginger, lemon juice.
  Examples of is_spice=false: chicken breast, rice, pasta, onion, bell pepper, canned tomatoes,
  olive oil (as cooking fat in quantity), butter (as main fat), cream, cheese, tofu.
  Rule of thumb: if you'd measure it in teaspoons/splashes rather than grams, it's is_spice=true.
— Set “quantity_grams”: 1 for all is_spice=true ingredients.
— List all is_spice=true ingredients AFTER all is_spice=false ingredients in the array.
— In steps, prefer 'spoon'/'teaspoon'/'splash' over grams for is_spice=true items.
{% endif %}
— Create a realistic plan for exactly one day with {{ meals_per_day }} meals
    for exactly {{ people_count }} people.
— All ingredient amounts in grams as numeric "quantity_grams". No units in name or quantity.
— Use {{ measurement_system }} measurement system in "steps". Keep using grams in "ingredients".

Output JSON schema (must match exactly):

{
  "meals": [
    {
      "name": <string>,
      "meal_type": "breakfast" | "lunch" | "dinner" | "snack",
      "meal_type_label": <string>,
      "ingredients": [
        {
          "name": <string>,
          "quantity_grams": <number>,
          "is_spice": <boolean>
        }
      ],
      "steps": [<string>]
    }
  ]
}

— Set "is_spice" following the pantry flavoring rule above. When in doubt: if you'd use it by feel rather than by weighing, set true.
— ALL output text (meal names, ingredient names, cooking steps, meal_type_label) MUST be written in {{ language or "English" }}.
— "meal_type" must ALWAYS be one of the English enum values above. "meal_type_label" is the display name in {{ language or "English" }}.

ALWAYS Return ONLY minified JSON. No explanations.